<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3823644>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Suta gaikhorstorum sp. nov. photographed in life from (A) 25 km W of Pannawonica, Western Australia, (B) 60 km S of Karratha, Western Australia, and (C) Hope Downs, Western Australia (images‒A, C: B. Maryan, B: B. Bush)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3823644/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3823638>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Dorsal head views and extent of dark hood on the nape in (A) WAM R20606 of Suta monachus, and (B) WAM R127817 of Suta gaikhorstorum sp. nov., and lateral head views showing the outlined number of primary (P) and secondary (S) temporals in (C) WAM R172448 of Suta monachus with 2 + 1, (D) WAM R20606 of Suta monachus with 1 + 1, and (E) WAM R127817 of Suta gaikhorstorum sp. nov. with 2 + 2 (images‒B.Maryan)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3823638/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3823642>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Preserved holotype WAM R127817 of Suta gaikhorstorum sp. nov. (image‒B. Maryan)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3823642/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3823640>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Map of Australia showing distribution of Suta monachus (circles) and Suta gaikhorstorum sp. nov. (triangles). White symbols indicate specimens examined in DNA analysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3823640/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3823646>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Representative habitat of Suta gaikhorstorum sp. nov., stony plain vegetated with dense Triodia and sparse Acacia at 22 km W of Pannawonica, Western Australia (image‒B. Bush)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3823646/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

